caption.body: This Pan Am postcard of a watercolor painting by John T. McCoy depicts a Lockheed Constellation flying over the San Francisco Bay in 1947 on the world’s first scheduled round-the-world commercial flight. You can also see San Francisco landmarks such as the Golden Gate Bridge and the Veterans Hospital.  John T. McCoy  Pan American World Airways postcard, Lockheed Constellation 1960s SFO Museum Collection Gift of Ernest J. Colant 1993.17.07
